## Why This Is Asked
This question tests the ability to coordinate three different CI tools to produce identical artifacts, including multi-arch builds, caching, security, and artifact promotion. It evaluates governance and practical implementation details, not abstractions.

## Key Concepts
- Build parity across CI ecosystems
- Docker Buildx multi-arch and cache strategies
- Base image digest pinning and SBOM generation
- Image signing with cosign and gate-based promotion
- Centralized configuration source (parity.json)

## Code Example
```json
// parity.json - single source of truth
{
  "base_images": {
    "api": "sha256:a1b2c3d4e5f6...",
    "worker": "sha256:f6e5d4c3b2a1..."
  },
  "build_args": {
    "NODE_VERSION": "20.11.0",
    "PYTHON_VERSION": "3.12"
  },
  "tool_versions": {
    "trivy": "0.48.0",
    "cosign": "2.2.0",
    "syft": "1.0.0"
  }
}
```

Each pipeline consumes this file to ensure consistent builds regardless of the CI system used.
